post_text: 4th grade families, make plans to attend instrument testing! 🎷🥁🎺
shared_text:
Central Lyon 5-8 Bands
June 18 at 2:26 PM ·

We are SO EXCITED 4th Grade Instrument Testing has been RESCHEDULED!
We will have Instrument Testing on Monday, June 29th from Noon-6:00pm in the High School Band Room.

4th grade families should check their e-mail for further information (or a letter will be coming in the mail.)

Our Display Night has also been rescheduled for Wednesday, July 8th at 6:30pm. This is the night families will sign their 4th grader up for band, summer band lessons, and receive their instrument & supplies.

Please help spread the word and share this post! We are SO EXCITED to finally start our 4th graders in Band!

post_text:
🎼🎹🥁🎷🎺🎵
Attention 4th graders (soon to be 5th graders):

Plan to attend Instrument Testing any time between Noon and 6:00 p.m. on Monday, June 15, in the High School Band Room. Please come even if you’re unsure of your interest in Band, or if you aren’t sure what instruments you’d like to try.

Only students are allowed to enter the building, but parents may wait in the parking lot while we take 15 minutes to test the instruments.

The Instrument Display Night will be at 6:30 p.m. Wednesday, June 24, in the HS Gym. This is the event when you will officially sign up for band, receive your instrument & supplies, sign up for beginner summer band lessons, and/or ask all of the questions!

Parents, please check your email for more information. If you have questions, please e-mail Mrs. Deutsch (edeutsch@centrallyon.org).

post_text: Students & Families - Mr Jorth would like to share what you can expect to pick up from the Central Lyon Post Office (aka elementary gym) today and tomorrow from 7:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. and on Friday until 1:00 p.m.
text: Students & Families - Mr Jorth would like to share what you can expect to pick up from the Central Lyon Post Office (aka elementary gym) today and tomorrow from 7:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. and on Friday until 1:00 p.m.

post_text:
The elementary gym has been transformed into a “post office” that will be open for students and families to pick up distance learning resources:
• Today, 3/25, from 7:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.
• Thursday, 3/26, from 7:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.
• Friday, 3/27, from 7:30 a.m. to 1:00 p.m.

Visitors should enter the elementary gym using the south entrance (bus drop-off and pick up lane). Central Lyon administrators will be onsite to enforce the following “stop the spread” strategies and social distancing techniques in order to protect the health and safety of all:

1. Only 10 individuals will be allowed access to the gymnasium at any one time.

2. All visitors will be restricted to the gymnasium.

3. Families will be limited to one (1) adult per family for collection of materials.

4. Student drivers (those with school permits or licenses) should attend by themselves.

More details about distance learning can be found in the Notice to Parents on the centrallyon.org website, under COVID-19 Updates.

Beginning today, FREE grab-and-go meals are available to all children/students age 18 and younger. This FREE meal will consist of a lunch and breakfast for the next day. Meals are provided Monday through Friday at the following locations:

Central Lyon School
Bus Drop-Off Lane / Entrance (south side of school)
11:30 a.m. - 12:30 p.m.

Doon
Public Library Parking Lot (look for the white school van)
11:30 a.m. - 12:00 p.m.

Meals may be delivered those outside the city limits of Rock Rapids and Doon. Call the high school office at (712) 472-2664 to request delivery.

• Free meals begin Monday, March 23 to all children/students 18 years of age and younger for grab-and-go service.

• Please encourage your students to not regroup and continue to practice social distancing.

Iowa Girls High School Athletic Union (IGHSAU)
January 27 at 10:30 AM ·

Member Monday Spotlight - Central Lyon

Central Lyon High School is located in Rock Rapids. The school has served the towns of Doon and Rock Rapids since 1959. Located in Lyon County, the Lions are members of the Siouxland Conference.

IGHSAU Did You Know? Central Lyon won the Class 1A Girls State Track & Field team championship in 2010.

#IGHSAUMemberMonday #IGHSAU #IowaGirl
